  <glossary>
    <definition id="import-auto-id3403668"><term>binding energy</term> <meaning id="fs-id1514269">the energy needed to separate nucleus into individual protons and neutrons</meaning></definition>
    <definition id="import-auto-id1577637"><term>binding energy per nucleon</term> <meaning id="fs-id2989927">the binding energy calculated per nucleon; it reveals the details of the nuclear force—larger the <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mtext>BE</m:mtext><m:mo stretchy="false">/</m:mo><m:mi>A</m:mi></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{"BE"/A} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, the more stable the nucleus</meaning></definition>
  </glossary>
